          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Bolsonaro’s invitation and passport</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-10-2.png" alt="Bolsonaro’s invitation and passport" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">​Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro wishes to attend Donald Trump’s inauguration but faces legal hurdles. Bolsonaro surrendered his passport while under investigation for allegedly orchestrating a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-h2-3-2023-coup-attempt" target="_blank">2023 coup attempt</a> to remain in power. Bolsonaro said he was honored by the invitation and thanked his son Eduardo Bolsonaro for maintaining close ties with the Trump family. Jair Bolsonaro is barred from assuming political office in Brazil till 2030 and faces criminal charges.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Bolsonaro and Trump have a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-h2-4-long-history" target="_blank">long history</a> that dates back to Trump's first term in office. During that time, Trump invited the right-wing leader to the Oval Office to discuss the possibility of toppling Venezuela's Nicolás Maduro. Both Trump and Bolsonaro have inspired loyal conservative movements in their respective countries. In addition, both presided over the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic, which drastically affected both countries.</p>
        </mj-text>
