          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Bedouin hostage body found</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israeli forces have retrieved the body of Bedouin Arab hostage Youssef al-Zayadna in a "complex and difficult operation" in Gaza. His body was recovered from an underground tunnel in Rafah and returned to Israel for identification. Al-Zayadna and his son Hamza were taken hostage during the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-h3-5-october-2023-hamas-attack" target="_blank">October 2023 Hamas attack</a> on Kibbutz Holit. Hamza's remains have not been recovered, though evidence suggests grave concerns for his life.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">There are around 300,000 Bedouin Arabs in Israel. They make up a subset of the 2 million Arabs in Israel. They have been doubly victimized by settling them in proximity to Hamas rockets and by state marginalization that has worsened since the October 2023 attack. Mediators Qatar, Egypt, and the U.S. are brokering a ceasefire and hostage deal. U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken stated that a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-h3-6-ceasefire-and-hostage-agreement" target="_blank">ceasefire and hostage agreement</a> is "very close." Israeli officials and families continue to push for the return of all hostages.
</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

