          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇨🇳 China: New Year tour of Africa</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">China's top diplomat, Wang Yi, began his annual New Year tour of Africa on Sunday. This is a 35-year tradition that underscores Beijing's steady engagement with the continent. Analysts claim that while Western powers are preoccupied with wars, domestic politics, and leadership transitions, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-br1-7-china-engagement-with-africa" target="_blank">China’s engagement with Africa</a> showcases consistency. Wang's visits to Namibia, the Republic of Congo, Chad, and Nigeria this week highlight China's focus on resource access, infrastructure development, and strengthening trade ties with the continent. Africa's 50-plus UN votes also position it as a key ally in China's push to reshape multilateral institutions and global norms.</p>
        </mj-text>
