          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇱🇧 Lebanon: President elected after 13 attempts</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Lebanon's army chief, Joseph Aoun, was elected president in the second round of the parliamentary votes. This is their <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-01-2025-br2-8-13th-attempt-to-elect" target="_blank">13th attempt to elect</a> a successor to Michel Aoun, whose term ended in 2022. Joseph Aoun received 99 votes out of 128 after failing to acquire a majority in the first round. In his speech to the parliament, Aoun pledged to fight corruption, control borders, discuss defense policy to remove Israeli occupation, and reconstruct the east and south that were affected by the war. World leaders, including Emmanuel Macron and Joe Biden, extended their warm congratulations by calling Aoun “the right leader for this time.”</p>
        </mj-text>
